.TH GIT-STAGE-BATCH 1 "March 2026" "git-stage-batch @VERSION@" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
git-stage-batch \- hunk-by-hunk and line-by-line staging for git
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git-stage-batch
[\fICOMMAND\fR [\fIARGS\fR...]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B git-stage-batch
provides a workflow for staging changes to git in a structured, reviewable way.
The tool works by finding hunks in your diff, presenting them one at a time,
and letting you include (stage), skip, or discard each hunk.
.PP
State is maintained in \fB.git/git-stage-batch/\fR so you can stop and continue
later, or run git commands between operations.
.SH COMMANDS
.SS Core Operations
.TP
.B start
Find and display the first unprocessed hunk; cache as "current".
Resets state if a session is already in progress.
.RS
.TP
.B \-U \fIN\fR, \-\-unified=\fIN\fR
Number of context lines in diff output (default: 3).
.RE
.TP
.B show
Reprint the cached "current" hunk.
Exit codes: 0 if hunk exists, 1 if no hunk.
.TP
.B include
Stage the cached hunk (entire hunk) to the index; advance to next.
When a session is active, running
.B git-stage-batch
with no command defaults to
.BR include .
.TP
.B skip
Mark the cached hunk as skipped; advance to next.
Skipped hunks can be revisited with
.BR again .
.TP
.B discard
Reverse-apply the cached hunk to the working tree; advance to next.
.B WARNING:
This permanently removes changes from your working tree.
.TP
.B status
Show session progress and remaining hunks.
.SS Session Management
.TP
.B again
Clear the blocklist and restart iteration through all hunks.
Useful for making another pass after committing some changes.
.TP
.B stop
End the current session and remove all state.
.TP
.B abort
Undo all changes made during the session, including commits and discards.
This resets HEAD to where you started, restores your original working tree,
and removes session state.
.B WARNING:
This will undo any commits made during the session.
.SS File-Level Operations
.TP
.B include \-\-file
Stage all hunks from the current file.
Advances to the next file after staging all hunks.
.TP
.B skip \-\-file
Skip all hunks from the current file.
All hunks from the file are marked as skipped and can be revisited with
.BR again .
.TP
.B discard \-\-file
Discard the entire current file from the working tree.
.B WARNING:
This permanently removes the entire file from your working tree.
.SS Permanent File Exclusion
.TP
.B block-file \fR[\fIPATH\fR]
Permanently exclude a file from all future sessions.
Adds the file to .gitignore, marks it as blocked in session state,
and skips all its hunks automatically.
When run without a current hunk, you can specify the file path.
.TP
.B unblock-file \fIPATH\fR
Remove a file from the blocked list.
Removes the file from .gitignore and the blocked files list,
allowing its hunks to be processed again.
